  'Mechanism',
  'Oxidative addition',
  'Organometallic catalysis',
  'A low-valent metal inserts into a sigma bond, commonly raising metal oxidation state and coordination number in cross-coupling cycles. | Often catalyst and aryl halide dependent; ligand electronics and halide identity strongly alter apparent rate. | Stereochemistry is substrate-specific; oxidative addition to vinyl electrophiles can preserve or alter geometry depending on pathway.',
  '',
  'Organometallic catalysis',
  '',
  0,
  '',
  '["cross-coupling","palladium","nickel","Suzuki-Miyaura coupling","Buchwald-Hartwig amination","Heck olefination","Sonogashira coupling"]',
