  'A poor leaving group is converted into a better one so substitution, elimination or coupling becomes kinetically feasible. | Often activation reagent and substrate concentration dependent, followed by nucleophile-dependent capture. | SN2 capture inverts stereocenters, while cationic pathways can scramble stereochemistry.',
