  'mechanism',
  'Mechanism',
  'ATRP activation-deactivation equilibrium',
  'Polymer mechanism',
  'Dormant alkyl halide chains reversibly form radicals under copper catalysis, limiting radical concentration and controlling chain growth. | Activation, deactivation and propagation terms combine; oxygen removes active Cu(I) catalyst. | Tacticity is usually not controlled unless monomer and catalyst design impose stereochemical bias.',
