  '{"id":"atrp-activation-deactivation","name":"ATRP activation-deactivation equilibrium","className":"Polymer mechanism","summary":"Dormant alkyl halide chains reversibly form radicals under copper catalysis, limiting radical concentration and controlling chain growth.","rateLaw":"Activation, deactivation and propagation terms combine; oxygen removes active Cu(I) catalyst.","stereo":"Tacticity is usually not controlled unless monomer and catalyst design impose stereochemical bias.","bestFor":["ATRP","block copolymers","surface-initiated polymer brushes","chain-end fidelity"],"steps":["Cu(I) activates alkyl halide","radical propagates","Cu(II) deactivates radical back to dormant chain"],"traps":["oxygen inhibition","loss of end-group fidelity","copper contamination"],"tags":["ATRP","polymer","radical"]}',
