  'mechanism:photoredox-quenching-cycle',
  'photoredox-quenching-cycle',
  'mechanism',
  'Mechanism',
  'Photoredox quenching cycle',
  'Photochemistry',
  'An excited photocatalyst transfers an electron or energy to a quencher, generating reactive open-shell intermediates under visible light. | Stern-Volmer quenching, light intensity and catalyst loading can define the kinetic boundary. | Stereochemical control is usually supplied by a second catalyst, substrate geometry or radical-pair environment.',
  '',
  'Photochemistry',
  '',
  0,
  '',
  '["photoredox","SET","light","visible-light catalysis","radical generation","decarboxylative coupling","diazonium arylation"]',
