  'mechanism',
  'Mechanism',
  'Meisenheimer SNAr pathway',
  'Aromatic substitution',
  'A nucleophile adds to an electron-poor aryl halide to form a sigma-adduct that eliminates leaving group and restores aromaticity. | Nucleophile and aryl electrophile terms are expected when addition is rate limiting. | No stereocenter is usually created at the aryl carbon; regioselectivity follows activating group placement.',
  '',
  'Aromatic substitution',
  '',
  0,
  '',
  '["SNAr","Meisenheimer","aryl fluoride","activated aryl fluorides","nitroarenes","heteroaryl substitution","medicinal chemistry diversification"]',
