  'mechanism mechanism acylium ion electrophilic aromatic substitution aromatic substitution a lewis acid activates an acid chloride or anhydride to generate an acylium-like electrophile that substitutes onto an aromatic ring. arene electronics electrophile generation and lewis acid stoichiometry govern observed rate. regiochemistry follows substituent directing effects stereochemistry is usually not central. aromatic substitution friedel-crafts eas acylium friedel-crafts acylation aryl ketone synthesis aromatic substitution teaching summary a lewis acid activates an acid chloride or anhydride to generate an acylium-like electrophile that substitutes onto an aromatic ring. steps acylium generation arene attack to sigma complex deprotonation and catalyst work-up best for friedel-crafts acylation aryl ketone synthesis aromatic substitution teaching rate law and stereochemistry arene electronics electrophile generation and lewis acid stoichiometry govern observed rate. regiochemistry follows substituent directing effects stereochemistry is usually not central.'
