  '{"id":"electrophile","term":"Electrophile","family":"Mechanism terminology","equation":"Nu: + E+ -> Nu-E","definition":"A reagent or site that accepts an electron pair from a nucleophile during bond formation.","academicUse":"Use the term to explain why carbonyl carbons, activated halogens and acylium ions can be attacked by electron-rich species.","evidenceNote":"A terminology-level claim should point to IUPAC; a substrate-specific claim needs experimental or computational support.","sourceRefs":["iupac-electrophile","iupac-goldbook"]}',
