  '{"id":"mechanism-evidence-stack","term":"Mechanism evidence stack","family":"Mechanistic reasoning","equation":"kinetics + isotope effects + stereochemistry + intermediates + controls -> mechanism argument","definition":"A layered way to describe how multiple measurements constrain plausible reaction mechanisms.","academicUse":"Use it when a named mechanism is tempting but insufficiently proven by product identity alone.","evidenceNote":"No single measurement normally proves a mechanism; it narrows alternatives.","sourceRefs":["iupac-goldbook","pubmed"]}',
  'concept concept mechanism evidence stack mechanistic reasoning a layered way to describe how multiple measurements constrain plausible reaction mechanisms. kinetics + isotope effects + stereochemistry + intermediates + controls - mechanism argument no single measurement normally proves a mechanism it narrows alternatives. mechanistic reasoning definition a layered way to describe how multiple measurements constrain plausible reaction mechanisms. equation kinetics + isotope effects + stereochemistry + intermediates + controls - mechanism argument evidence note no single measurement normally proves a mechanism it narrows alternatives.'
);
