  '{"id":"spectral-triangulation","title":"Spectral Triangulation Protocol","domain":"Analytical chemistry","level":"Core","summary":"Ranks a structural assignment by the number and independence of supporting spectral observations.","inputs":["IR bands","1H NMR features","13C NMR features","MS pattern","Purity notes"],"outputs":["Assignment confidence","Conflicting evidence","Missing experiment","Reference comparison target"],"checklist":["At least two independent observations support the same functional group.","A diagnostic peak is not treated as complete structure proof.","Integration, multiplicity and chemical shift are interpreted together.","Impurity, solvent and concentration artefacts are considered."],"example":"A carbonyl IR band supports a carbonyl class; an aldehydic 1H signal and 13C carbonyl resonance make the aldehyde claim stronger."}',
  'method method spectral triangulation protocol analytical chemistry core ranks a structural assignment by the number and independence of supporting spectral observations. analytical chemistry core inputs ir bands 1h nmr features 13c nmr features ms pattern purity notes workflow outputs assignment confidence conflicting evidence missing experiment reference comparison target quality controls'
);
