  '{"id":"mechanism-discrimination","title":"Mechanism Discrimination Protocol","domain":"Physical organic chemistry","level":"Advanced","summary":"Uses substrate structure, solvent, stereochemistry, rate law and product distribution to choose between plausible mechanisms.","inputs":["Substrate class","Nucleophile or base","Solvent","Stereochemical result","Rate data"],"outputs":["Mechanism hypothesis","Evidence for","Evidence against","Decisive missing test"],"checklist":["A mechanism is treated as a constrained hypothesis rather than a memorized label.","Rate-law evidence is separated from stereochemical evidence.","Competing pathways are named when the same conditions could support them.","The weakest assumption is explicitly identified."],"example":"A primary substrate and strong nucleophile support SN2, but solvent and steric context still matter."}',
