  'halogen-isotope',
  'spectroscopy',
  'Spectroscopy',
  'Halogen isotope pattern audit',
  'Mass spectrometry',
  ' | Does the molecular ion region support chlorine or bromine substitution? | A near 1:1 M/M+2 pattern is strong evidence for bromine, subject to molecular-ion assignment.',
  '',
  'Mass spectrometry',
  '',
  0,
  '',
  '[]',
  'record.html?type=spectroscopy&id=halogen-isotope',
  'spectroscopy.html?id=halogen-isotope',
  'data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20width%3D%22640%22%20height%3D%22420%22%20viewBox%3D%220%200%20640%20420%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%22640%22%20height%3D%22420%22%20fill%3D%22%23f5f5f7%22%2F%3E%3Cpath%20d%3D%22M84%20278%20190%2096l106%20182H84Zm260-152h170v170H344V126Zm-174%2044h276%22%20fill%3D%22none%22%20stroke%3D%22%231d1d1f%22%20stroke-width%3D%2212%22%20stroke-linecap%3D%22round%22%20stroke-linejoin%3D%22round%22%20opacity%3D%22.34%22%2F%3E%3Ccircle%20cx%3D%22190%22%20cy%3D%2296%22%20r%3D%2220%22%20fill%3D%22%230071e3%22%2F%3E%3Ccircle%20cx%3D%22296%22%20cy%3D%22278%22%20r%3D%2220%22%20fill%3D%22%230071e3%22%2F%3E%3Ccircle%20cx%3D%22514%22%20cy%3D%22126%22%20r%3D%2218%22%20fill%3D%22%230071e3%22%2F%3E%3Ctext%20x%3D%2242%22%20y%3D%2258%22%20fill%3D%22%231d1d1f%22%20font-family%3D%22-apple-system%2CBlinkMacSystemFont%2CSegoe%20UI%2CArial%2Csans-serif%22%20font-size%3D%2224%22%20font-weight%3D%22700%22%3ESpectroscopy%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Ctext%20x%3D%2242%22%20y%3D%22355%22%20fill%3D%22%231d1d1f%22%20font-family%3D%22-apple-system%2CBlinkMacSystemFont%2CSegoe%20UI%2CArial%2Csans-serif%22%20font-size%3D%2236%22%20font-weight%3D%22800%22%3EHalogen%20isotope%20pattern%20audi%3C%2Ftext%3E%3Ctext%20x%3D%2242%22%20y%3D%22388%22%20fill%3D%22%236e6e73%22%20font-family%3D%22-apple-system%2CBlinkMacSystemFont%2CSegoe%20UI%2CArial%2Csans-serif%22%20font-size%3D%2220%22%20font-weight%3D%22600%22%3EMass%20spectrometry%3C%2Ftext%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E',
  '{"id":"halogen-isotope","title":"Halogen isotope pattern audit","family":"Mass spectrometry","confidence":80,"question":"Does the molecular ion region support chlorine or bromine substitution?","signals":[{"technique":"MS","signal":"M and M+2 pair","interpretation":"Halogen isotope pattern","strength":"strong"},{"technique":"MS","signal":"ca. 1:1 intensity","interpretation":"Bromine is more likely than chlorine","strength":"strong"},{"technique":"IR/NMR","signal":"No direct halogen proof","interpretation":"Other spectra constrain structure but do not replace isotope evidence","strength":"limiting"}],"conclusion":"A near 1:1 M/M+2 pattern is strong evidence for bromine, subject to molecular-ion assignment.","missing":"High-resolution mass and formula constraint."}',
  'spectroscopy spectroscopy halogen isotope pattern audit mass spectrometry does the molecular ion region support chlorine or bromine substitution a near 1 1 m m+2 pattern is strong evidence for bromine subject to molecular-ion assignment. mass spectrometry question does the molecular ion region support chlorine or bromine substitution signals ms m and m+2 pair halogen isotope pattern ms ca. 1 1 intensity bromine is more likely than chlorine ir nmr no direct halogen proof other spectra constrain structure but do not replace isotope evidence assignments conclusion a near 1 1 m m+2 pattern is strong evidence for bromine subject to molecular-ion assignment.'
);
